revised_title: Natural Curiosities of New England: Dwarfish Oaks, Bark with Sanative Properties, and a Strange Fish
tldr: The author, John Winthrop, describes various natural curiosities found in New England, including dwarfish oaks, a tree bark with healing properties, and a strange fish with unique features. He also discusses the possibility of further research on these discoveries and their potential implications.
